[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Greetings from Rome. I propose a clear division of the Balkans: Italy will focus on the Mediterranean and Tunis, leaving the Balkans to Austria. I have no designs on Trieste this year - my fleet moves south toward Ionian and my army toward Tunis. In return, I ask that you keep your fleet in Trieste and not threaten Venice. A stable northern border benefits us both while we expand. Shall we formalize this arrangement?'}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Fellow Mediterranean power - I suggest we avoid conflict in our early expansion. Italy moves toward Tunis and the western Mediterranean; Turkey should focus on the Black Sea and Balkans. I propose we each respect the other's sphere: Greece is yours if you want it, I will not contest it this year. In return, keep your fleets away from the Ionian. A non-aggression pact between us allows both nations to grow at others' expense."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'France and Italy share no natural conflict - our interests diverge geographically. I propose Italy takes Tunis while France secures Iberia. I will not move into Piedmont or threaten Marseilles, and I ask the same courtesy regarding my northern territories. A friendly Italy on your southeastern flank is far preferable to a hostile one. Let us coordinate to ensure neither Austria nor Germany grows too powerful in the center.'}]
