[{'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "Greetings from London. I propose a cordial understanding between our nations - France and England need not be rivals in this opening phase. I intend to focus my naval power northward toward Norway and Scandinavia, leaving the English Channel and your western approaches unmolested. In return, I ask that you keep Brest's fleet out of the Channel and focus your energies southward toward Iberia and the Mediterranean. A mutual non-aggression pact in the west benefits us both enormously. What say you?"}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "A word from England: I see opportunity for cooperation between our nations. I propose we divide the northern neutrals sensibly - I will move to Norway via the North Sea, while you take Denmark and Holland. This keeps us from stepping on each other's toes and maximizes both our gains. I have no designs on Kiel or the German coast. Can we agree on this division? I'd also welcome your thoughts on containing Russian expansion in the north."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Greetings from London. England and Russia have historically found common cause when it suits both powers. I intend to move into Norway this spring - I trust this does not conflict with your interests, as your fleet at St. Petersburg is better positioned to support your southern ambitions. I would welcome an understanding that we respect each other's spheres: Scandinavia for England, the Black Sea region for Russia. Let us not waste energy competing where cooperation serves us better."}]
