[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Greetings from Vienna. I propose we establish a clear understanding from the outset: I have no designs on Venice, and I hope you have none on Trieste. Let us both focus our energies outward - I intend to move on Serbia and Romania, while you push south and west. A non-aggression pact between us frees both our hands considerably. I suggest F TRI moves to Albania or Adriatic, not toward Venice, as a show of good faith - but I need the same assurance that A VEN stays away from Trieste. Agreed?'}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Fellow power of the southeast, I write to propose coordination. I intend to take Serbia and Romania - these are natural Austrian gains. I have no interest in Bulgaria or the Balkans beyond Serbia. If you move into Bulgaria, we need not clash. In fact, a joint approach to the Balkans where I take SER/RUM and you take BUL/GRE would serve us both well against Russian expansion. Russia is the common threat - F SEV eyes Romania just as much as I do. Shall we coordinate to contain them?'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'I write in the spirit of early cooperation. Austria and Russia need not be enemies - the Balkans are large enough for both of us to expand without conflict. I propose we respect a simple division: I will pursue Serbia and Romania, and I ask that you keep Galicia neutral and focus your energies northward and eastward. In return, I will not threaten Warsaw or any Russian territory. A stable southern flank benefits us both as we each face other pressures. What are your intentions regarding Galicia and Romania?'}]
