[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, let us establish a firm understanding from the outset. Germany has no designs on Vienna or Budapest - our expansion lies westward toward France and northward toward Scandinavia. I propose we coordinate: you push south and east against Italy and the Balkans, while I handle the western front. Specifically, I intend to move into Denmark and Holland this spring. I ask only that you keep your armies away from Bohemia and Silesia - those are German buffer zones. In return, I will support your moves against Serbia or Rumania. A strong Austria-Germany axis benefits us both enormously.'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, Germany seeks a non-aggression understanding with you in the early game. I am moving my forces westward - toward Denmark, Holland, and eventually France. I have no interest in Warsaw or the eastern territories at this stage. I propose we respect a clear boundary: Prussia and Silesia remain German, and I will not contest your moves into Galicia or Rumania. A quiet eastern front serves us both while we expand in our natural directions. What are your intentions regarding Scandinavia? I would prefer we not compete there - perhaps Sweden for you, Denmark for me?'}, {'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "England, I want to be direct with you: Germany's fleet moves to Denmark this spring, and my army moves toward Holland. These are natural German interests. I propose we avoid conflict in the North Sea - you take Norway, I take Denmark and Sweden, and we leave each other's home territories untouched. France is the common threat to both of us on the continent. A Germany-England understanding against France would be mutually profitable. I am willing to coordinate specifically: if you pressure France from Brest, I will push through Burgundy. Let us discuss terms."}]
