[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, your proposal aligns well with my intentions. I confirm: F ANK moves to BLA, A CON moves to BUL. I will not move into ARM this year. In return, I expect F SEV to move to RUM as you stated, leaving BLA clear. This gives us both clean expansion - you take RUM, I take BUL. We can discuss coordinating against Austria in future phases once we've both secured these gains. Do not betray this arrangement - I will remember it."}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, your proposal is acceptable. I will take BUL, you take SER and RUM - we need not clash. However, I must warn you: Russia has told me they intend to contest RUM with F SEV moving there this spring. You may face a collision in RUM. I suggest you move A BUD to RUM with support from A VIE to SER, ensuring you hold RUM against Russian interference. Turkey will not interfere in SER or RUM - those are yours. Let us both profit while Russia overextends.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, agreed on spheres of influence. I will focus on BLA and BUL; you take Tunis and the western Mediterranean. Greece can wait - I have no fleet moving there this year. Keep your fleet out of the Aegean and Eastern Mediterranean and we have no quarrel. A Turkish-Italian non-aggression pact through 1902 serves us both well. Let us each grow at the expense of others and revisit our arrangement when the board develops.'}]
