[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Agreed. Russia confirms: F SEV moves to RUM this spring, not BLA or ARM. I expect F ANK to BLA and A CON to BUL as you proposed. This gives us both clean expansion - you take Bulgaria, I take Romania. Neither of us wastes units fighting each other while Austria sits in BUD watching. After 1901, we should discuss coordinating against Austria together - BUD and VIE are ripe targets if we align. Hold to this arrangement and Russia will be a reliable partner in the south.'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, I have heard your proposal and I am willing to keep Galicia neutral in 1901 - A WAR will not move to GAL this spring. However, Romania is within Russia's natural sphere and I intend to take it with F SEV. I ask that you not contest RUM this year - focus your energies on Serbia and the western Balkans. If we respect this division, we can both expand without conflict and discuss further cooperation against Italy or Turkey in 1902. Galicia remains untouched by me this year - I give you my word."}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Germany, we are aligned. Russia will take Norway via F STP/SC this spring and focus on Romania in the south. I have no interest in Prussia, Silesia, or Sweden - Denmark is yours, Sweden I may contest later but not at your expense. Keep your forces westward and we will have no quarrel. A quiet eastern front is exactly what both of us need in 1901. Let us revisit coordination in 1902 once we have both expanded.'}]
