[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Excellent - we are in agreement. My specific orders this spring: F TRI moves to ALB (away from Venice), A BUD moves to SER, A VIE moves to GAL. I expect A VEN to stay in VEN or move south/west, not toward TRI. This arrangement serves us both well - you take TUN and the Mediterranean, I take SER and RUM. Let us build on this foundation in future seasons.'}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'We are aligned. My moves this spring: A BUD to SER, A VIE to GAL, F TRI to ALB. I will not contest BUL or GRE - those are yours. I ask only that you do not move into SER or RUM, which are my targets. With Austria taking SER/RUM and Turkey taking BUL/GRE, we create a strong Balkan bloc that Russia cannot easily penetrate. F SEV is the common threat to RUM - if you can pressure them from the south, I will push from the north.'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, I appreciate your cooperative tone. My plans are clear: A BUD to SER, A VIE to GAL (purely defensive positioning, not threatening WAR), F TRI to ALB. I ask that A WAR does NOT move to GAL - that would be seen as hostile and force me to respond. Keep WAR in place or move it north, and we maintain peace. Romania is my target via BUD next year - I ask you not to contest it with SEV. A stable Austro-Russian border in Galicia benefits us both while we each expand in our natural directions.'}]
