[{'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, your proposal suits me well. I confirm: my fleets move north toward Norway, and I have no designs on the Channel or your western coast. You take Spain and Portugal, I take Norway and Belgium. Let us also keep a watchful eye on Germany - their fleet moves to Denmark and army toward Holland, which is aggressive expansion. If Germany overreaches, we should be prepared to coordinate. For now, let us grow in peace and revisit our arrangement once we've both secured our initial gains."}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Germany, I accept your proposal on the northern neutrals - Norway for England, Denmark and Sweden for Germany. I will not contest your moves in Scandinavia. However, I must be candid: I am not prepared to pressure France militarily at this stage, as it would expose my home centers unnecessarily. What I can offer is neutrality and intelligence sharing. Let us first secure our respective gains, then reassess the French question together. Agreed?'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, I appreciate your silence on Norway - I take it as tacit acceptance of my move there. I confirm my fleet moves north and I have no hostile intentions toward St. Petersburg. I would suggest we formalize our understanding: England controls Norway and the North Sea, Russia focuses on Sweden via Finland and the Black Sea region. A stable northern arrangement benefits us both and lets us focus on the real threats - a growing Germany or an aggressive Austria. I look forward to continued cooperation.'}]
