[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, our positions remain complementary. I'm moving F ION to TUN this fall to secure that supply center, with A APU in support. A TYR holds position for now - I have no designs on TRI or VIE this year. I trust you're continuing your eastern push against Russia and Turkey. Let's keep our understanding intact and discuss 1902 coordination next round."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, I'm taking Tunis this fall as planned - F ION to TUN, A APU supports. Greece is yours if you want it; I have no fleet moving to AEG or GRE. I'd like to discuss a longer-term arrangement: you focus on the Black Sea and Balkans, I focus on the western Mediterranean. We can be powerful allies if we avoid stepping on each other. What are your intentions for Greece this fall?"}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, I'm focused entirely on Tunis this fall and have no interest in Marseilles or Piedmont. My A TYR is positioned defensively - I'm watching Germany and Austria, not you. If Germany becomes a problem for either of us, we should talk. For now, let's maintain our friendly understanding and stay out of each other's way."}]
