GER
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "England, the fall moves are critical. I am taking DEN (already secured) and moving A KIE to HOL and A RUH to BEL - this gives us both maximum expansion. France in BUR is a direct threat to both of us. I propose you move F NTH to support my HOL grab, and we coordinate a joint squeeze on France next year. I will not move into BEL if you want it, but HOL is mine. Confirm your intentions regarding Norway and whether you'll pressure France from the channel."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, our non-aggression holds firm. I am focused entirely westward - HOL and BEL are my targets this fall. I have no units moving east of Berlin. Austria is overextended in the Balkans - you should press your advantage in Galicia and Romania. I suggest we maintain our understanding through 1902 while we both consolidate. What are your intentions regarding Sweden? I am taking Scandinavia from the south but have no objection to you securing Norway via your northern fleet.'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, good progress in the Balkans - Serbia secured is excellent. I am moving to consolidate HOL and BEL this fall, expanding westward as planned. I need you to hold Bohemia as our shared buffer - no Italian or Russian units should threaten that corridor. Italy in Tyrolia concerns me - what are your intentions regarding Venice and the Italian front? A coordinated German-Austrian pressure on Italy could open opportunities for both of us in 1902.'}]
--------------
RUS
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Our arrangement from spring has played out perfectly - I hold RUM, you hold BUL, and the Black Sea remains yours. I propose we continue this cooperation into fall and beyond. My F RUM will hold position securing that center. I suggest we coordinate against Austria - their A GAL threatens both of us. If you move A BUL toward SER and I pressure from the north, we can carve up Austrian territory between us. What are your intentions for CON and ANK this fall?'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "I see you've taken SER and GAL - well played. I want to be direct: I have no hostile intentions toward Austria at this time. My F RUM is simply securing that neutral center, not threatening BUD. However, I am concerned about your A GAL sitting adjacent to my territory. I propose we formalize a non-aggression pact - GAL stays Austrian, I keep RUM and Ukraine, and we both focus our expansion elsewhere. Turkey is the common threat in the Balkans. What are your fall orders?"}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Good progress in spring - you've secured Denmark. Our eastern non-aggression arrangement continues to serve us both well. I'm consolidating in RUM and the south this fall. I trust you're pushing west against England and France? A strong Germany in the west keeps pressure off both of us. I intend to move F STP/SC toward Norway or Sweden to expand north - no conflict with your interests. Confirm we remain aligned."}]
