FRA
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "Fall 1901: I'm moving F MAO to POR and A SPA holds to secure the SC. A BUR moves to BEL — this is the move we discussed, and I need you to stay out of BEL this fall so we don't bounce each other. You take NOR and HOL if you can reach it; I take BEL and POR. That's two builds each and we both come out of 1901 strong. Confirm you're not contesting BEL and we proceed as agreed."}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Fall 1901: A BUR is moving to BEL, not MUN — I have no interest in your home centers this year. I'd prefer we establish a working arrangement: you consolidate DEN and HOL, I consolidate Iberia and BEL. The real threat to both of us is a strong ENG or a resurgent Russia. If you're open to coordinating against either, I'm listening. What are your fall intentions?"}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Fall 1901: Confirming our arrangement holds — MAR is secure, I'm not moving into PIE or TYR. I'm pushing west toward Iberia and BEL. Austria looks aggressive with SER and GAL already taken — you may want to pressure TRI or VEN to keep them honest. I can offer diplomatic cover if you move against Austria; it keeps them from consolidating the Balkans unchallenged. What's your fall plan?"}]
