ENG
[{'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "Good news from London - our spring arrangements worked perfectly. I have F NTH positioned and F ENG in the Channel. I intend to move F NTH to NOR this fall to secure Norway as agreed, while F ENG moves to BEL - which I trust you have no objection to, as we discussed. I will not threaten your western coast. I note GER has taken DEN and is eyeing HOL - a growing German fleet is a concern for both of us. Let's keep communication open about GER's expansion."}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Spring went well for both of us. I'm moving F NTH to NOR this fall to secure that center. I also intend F ENG to BEL - I trust you have no objection since HOL is your natural sphere. I note FRA has A BUR sitting uncomfortably close to your territory - if you're planning to push back against FRA, I'm open to discussing coordination in 1902. For now, let's confirm: NOR for ENG, DEN+HOL for GER, BEL for ENG. Does that still hold?"}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, I've been trying to reach you. To be direct: I am taking Norway this fall - F NTH moves to NOR. I have no designs on Sweden or St. Petersburg, which I consider your natural sphere. I'd welcome a clear understanding that we respect each other's northern interests. What are your intentions regarding Scandinavia?"}]
