TUR
[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Comrade, our Spring arrangement worked perfectly - you hold RUM, I hold BUL, and the Black Sea is secured between us. For Fall, I propose: F BLA supports your F RUM to hold against any Austrian pressure, while A BUL moves to GRE (securing another center for me) and A CON moves to SMY or holds. Austria has A SER adjacent to both RUM and BUL - they are the common threat. I suggest we coordinate to keep Austria contained. What are your Fall intentions? I want to ensure we don't accidentally clash."}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, our arrangement from Spring holds - you took SER as agreed, I took BUL. For Fall, I intend A BUL to move to GRE, which is firmly in my sphere. I would ask that you keep A SER away from BUL and RUM - Russia's F RUM is already there and any Austrian move risks a three-way conflict that benefits neither of us. Let us maintain our respective spheres: you consolidate in the Balkans north of BUL, I expand south into GRE. What are your Fall moves?"}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, our non-aggression pact from Spring served us both well. For Fall, I am moving A BUL to GRE - I want to confirm you have no designs on Greece this season, as your F ION is in the area. Greece is my natural expansion and I expect you to respect that. In return, I will keep my forces away from the Ionian and support your western Mediterranean ambitions. Please confirm GRE is mine this Fall and we maintain our understanding.'}]
