AUT
[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'I want to be direct with you: my A GAL is positioned to move to RUM this fall, and I intend to do so. Russia already holds SEV and has strong northern centers - RUM is critical for Austrian expansion. I propose we avoid a costly standoff: let me take RUM uncontested this fall, and in return I will support your interests against Turkey in the Black Sea region and keep A GAL out of UKR/WAR permanently. If you contest RUM with F RUM, we both lose a turn and create an opening for Turkey to grow unchecked. A cooperative arrangement benefits us both far more than a clash over one center.'}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Our arrangement from spring holds - I'm taking SER (already done) and pushing toward RUM, while you consolidate BUL and GRE. I'd like to propose F ALB moves to GRE this fall to secure it, with your A BUL supporting from the south if needed. This keeps GRE in friendly hands and blocks Italy from expanding north. In exchange, I will not contest BUL or CON - those are yours. Russia is the common threat we both face; let's grow our positions before dealing with them."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Our non-aggression pact continues to serve us both well. I note A TYR is adjacent to VIE and TRI - I trust this is simply a transit position and not a threat to my home centers. To maintain our good relations, I'd ask that A TYR move south toward VEN or west toward MUN rather than pressing toward Austrian territory. In return, I will keep my forces focused eastward on RUM and the Balkans and will not threaten VEN or TYR. Let's both grow at the expense of others rather than each other."}]
INFO:main:Negotiation sub-round 2/2
