FRA
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "England, I see the problem: you're moving F ENG to BEL and I'm moving A BUR to BEL — we bounce and both lose the center. One of us must stand down. I propose this: you take BEL with F ENG, I redirect A BUR to MUN instead. You get BEL and NOR, I get POR and MUN. That's still two builds each and we don't waste the fall on a collision. If you prefer I take BEL and you redirect elsewhere, say so — but we need to resolve this now. I'm prepared to honor whichever split you confirm, but silence means we bounce."}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, final round so I'll be direct: A BUR is moving to MUN this fall. I have no interest in a prolonged western war — I want Iberia secured and a stable eastern frontier. If you want to avoid losing MUN, support it from RUH and we can negotiate a division of influence afterward. Alternatively, if you're willing to cede MUN and work with me against England's growing naval position, I can offer you a free hand in Scandinavia and the east. Your call — but the move is coming."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, understood on Tunis — good move. Austria has SER and GAL already; if F ALB moves to GRE this fall they'll have four centers and be the dominant Balkan power before we can respond. I'd encourage you to think about TRI now rather than later — a supported move from TYR or APU into TRI while Austria is stretched would check their growth before it becomes a problem for both of us. I'm not asking you to fight my wars, but a weaker Austria benefits us both."}]
