GER
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "Confirmed: NOR for ENG, DEN+HOL for GER, BEL for ENG. My orders this fall: F DEN holds or moves to support, A KIE moves to HOL, A RUH moves to BEL - wait, I will cede BEL to you. A RUH moves to MUN to free up positioning. Actually let me be precise: A KIE - HOL, A RUH - BEL is what I originally planned, but if you want BEL, I'll redirect A RUH to MUN instead. You take BEL, I take HOL. France in BUR is a problem for 1902 - I propose we both squeeze France hard next year. Your F ENG can threaten BRE while I push through BUR. Agreed?"}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'France, I appreciate the transparency. I am taking HOL this fall - that is non-negotiable. If you are moving A BUR to BEL, that actually suits me fine as it keeps you away from MUN. However, understand this clearly: if any French unit threatens Munich or Ruhr in 1902, I will treat it as an act of war and coordinate with England against you. If you genuinely want a working arrangement, keep your units south and west - Iberia and MAR are your sphere, not the Rhine. Demonstrate good faith by keeping BUR clear in 1902 and we can discuss longer-term cooperation against Russia or England.'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, we remain aligned. I am pushing west - HOL secured this fall, then BEL and beyond in 1902. Your northern fleet moving toward Norway is fine by me - Sweden I intend to take eventually but Norway is yours. One thing: Austria is getting strong in the Balkans with Serbia and Galicia secured. You should press them hard in 1902 - Galicia is vulnerable and RUM gives you leverage. A weakened Austria benefits us both. I will keep German units west of Silesia as promised. Let's both expand aggressively this year and reassess in 1902."}]
