ENG
[{'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Good morning from London. We've both done well in 1901 - you hold HOL and DEN, I hold BEL and NWY. Now let's talk 1902. France sits at 5 centers with SPA, POR, and BUR threatening your southern flank. I propose we coordinate: I can move F BEL to support pressure on France from the north, while you push A RUH toward BUR or MUN. France must not be allowed to grow further. What are your intended moves this spring? I want to ensure we don't work at cross-purposes."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "Greetings from London. We both achieved our 1901 goals cleanly - BEL for me, POR and SPA for you. I want to maintain our cordial arrangement. My concern this spring is Germany - they hold DEN, HOL, and have armies positioned aggressively. I intend to keep F BEL in a defensive posture for now. I would ask: what are your intentions with A BUR this spring? If you're pushing into Germany, I could potentially coordinate from the north. Let's not let Germany grow unchecked."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Hello from London. Our northern arrangement worked perfectly - NWY for me, BOT for your fleet. I trust you're eyeing Sweden this spring with F BOT. I intend to move F NWY toward SWE or hold - I will NOT contest Sweden, that remains your sphere as agreed. My focus is on the western continent. I'd appreciate knowing your broader strategic intentions so we can avoid any accidental friction in Scandinavia."}]
--------------
ITA
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, I want to maintain our cooperative relationship. My units are positioned at TRI, APU, and TUN - I have no aggressive intentions toward your home centers this season. I'm watching Germany's growth with concern (5 centers already) and suggest we both focus on containing them. I plan to move A TRI toward VIE or TYR to pressure Germany from the south - this actually helps you. Can you confirm your intentions regarding Greece and the Balkans? I want to ensure we don't accidentally clash."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, the situation is favorable for both of us. Austria failed to take Greece last fall - F ALB bounced with your A BUL. I suggest you push A BUL to GRE this spring while F BLA secures your position. I will move F TUN to ION to support your Aegean operations and keep Austria's F ALB occupied. Together we can squeeze Austria from both sides - you take GRE, I pressure TRI. This is the moment to act. Confirm your moves and let's coordinate."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, Austria now holds 4 centers (BUD, VIE, WAR, SER) and is the fastest growing power on the board. I'm moving against TRI this season - A TRI to BUD or VIE, supported if possible. I need you to keep pressure on Germany so they cannot assist Austria. If you can push into MUN or RUH, it pins Germany and gives me a free hand in the east. In return, I'll stay out of MAR and PIE - the western Mediterranean is yours. Let's coordinate to cut Austria down before they dominate the center."}]
--------------
TUR
[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Comrade, our alliance continues to serve us both well. Austria is the clear threat - they hold WAR (your home!), SER, and their F ALB is positioned aggressively in the Balkans. I propose we coordinate directly against Austria this spring. I can move A BUL to RUM to support your F RUM holding or advancing, while F BLA continues to secure the Black Sea for us both. Alternatively, I can push A BUL into SER if you want to squeeze Austria from multiple directions. What is your plan for A SEV and F RUM this turn? Let's coordinate precisely so we don't waste moves."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Friend, our non-aggression pact has served us both well - you secured TRI and TUN, I secured BUL. Austria now holds TRI's home center and is expanding aggressively with units in SER, ALB, and WAR. They are becoming the dominant Balkan power and a threat to both of us. I intend to push into GRE this spring with A BUL. Would you consider moving F TUN toward ION or having A TRI press against Austria? A coordinated squeeze on Austria benefits us both enormously. What are your intentions for 1902?"}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, let us be direct: your F ALB contesting Greece last fall was a violation of our agreed spheres. Greece is mine - I will be taking it this spring with A BUL. I have no desire for conflict with you, but I will not tolerate further encroachment into my sphere. Focus your energies northward against Russia, who holds your home center of WAR. I can support your efforts against Russia if you respect the Balkans south of SER as Turkish territory. What do you say?'}]
--------------
GER
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "England, France has shown its true colors - last fall A BUR attempted to take MUN directly, a naked act of aggression against Germany. I successfully defended, but France must be punished. I propose we coordinate a joint assault on France this spring: I will move A RUH into BUR and A HOL supports or advances toward BEL. If you move F BEL to support my push into BUR, or advance toward PAR, we can crack France open together. I will take BUR and push toward PAR while you secure the Atlantic coast. France with 5 centers is a threat to both of us - let's cut them down to size now. What specific moves can you commit to?"}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, our non-aggression holds firm and I see no reason to change that. France attacked my home center last fall and I am now turning west to deal with them. I have no designs east of Berlin - you have my word. I would ask only that you keep Austria occupied in the east so they don't interfere in my western campaign. A strong Germany and Russia dividing Europe between us is far preferable to letting France or England dominate. Are you pressing Austria or Turkey this season?"}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, France attacked MUN last fall - a direct provocation I will not forget. I am turning my full attention west. This means my eastern flank needs to be secure. I ask that you hold your current positions and not advance toward Silesia or Bohemia - I have no hostile intent toward you and wish to maintain our cooperative relationship. In return, I will not interfere in your Balkan operations. What are your plans for 1902 - are you pressing Serbia further south or dealing with Russia?'}]
--------------
AUT
[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, we've maintained good relations and I want to keep it that way. I propose a concrete arrangement for 1902: I will not contest Trieste or any Italian home center, and in return I ask that you keep A TRI out of Serbia and BUD. My focus is on the Balkans - specifically Greece and eventually Bulgaria. I'd like to coordinate against Turkey together: if you move F TUN toward ION and I push F ALB to GRE, we can squeeze Turkey from two sides. What are your intentions this spring? Let's be specific so we don't accidentally clash."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, let's be direct: last fall we both moved on Greece and bounced each other, which helped nobody. I'm willing to concede Greece to you IF you support my move against Russia - specifically, if A BUL supports A SER into RUM, we split the gains and both grow. Russia is the real threat to both of us. F RUM sitting there blocks my expansion and threatens your Black Sea position long-term. Let's coordinate: A BUL supports A SER - RUM, F ALB moves to ION or ADR to stay out of your way. What do you say?"}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, I want to avoid unnecessary conflict between us. My A WAR is in Warsaw - your home center - and I have no intention of holding it against you permanently. I propose a clean swap: I will move A WAR to GAL this spring, vacating Warsaw, and in return you move F RUM to BUL or SEV, allowing me to take RUM peacefully. We both gain: you get Warsaw back, I get RUM, and we avoid a costly war. If you refuse, I will be forced to coordinate with Turkey and Italy against you. This is a genuine offer - let's resolve this diplomatically."}]
--------------
RUS
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Comrade, our alliance continues to serve us both well. This spring I intend to push aggressively against Austria - I propose F RUM moves to BUL (with your support if possible), while A SEV moves to ARM to threaten ANK/CON from the north as a feint to keep Turkey's neighbors nervous... wait, I mean to coordinate: I want F RUM -> BUL supported by A BUL if you move A BUL elsewhere, or alternatively F RUM -> SEV while A UKR -> WAR to take back my home center from Austria. My primary target is WAR (Austrian-held). I need you to hold BLA and keep pressure on AUT's southern flank via SER/BUL. Can A BUL move to GRE or SER to pressure Austria while I push from the north? Let's coordinate specific moves."}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, you hold WAR which is a Russian home center - this is an unacceptable situation that I intend to rectify this spring. I am moving A UKR to WAR. You can either vacate peacefully and we discuss a cooperative arrangement against Turkey, or we go to war. I have no interest in your Balkan centers if you return WAR. Choose wisely - I have Turkish support on my southern flank and can afford a prolonged conflict with you.'}, {'recipients': ['ENG', 'GER'], 'body': 'Gentlemen, the situation in central Europe is developing well. I am focused entirely on reclaiming WAR from Austria and expanding southward. F BOT will move to SWE this spring - I trust England has no objection given our prior understanding that Sweden falls in my sphere. Germany, I assume you continue westward - no conflict between us in the east. Let us all prosper by focusing on our respective theaters.'}]
