FRA
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'England — confirmed: A BUR moves to MUN this spring, A SPA to GAS. Germany is the target. I need you to move F BEL to HOL or support a push on HOL from BEL — that pins Germany from two directions simultaneously and we split the gains. You take HOL, I take MUN. If you hold BEL passive, Germany can concentrate against me alone. This is the moment to act — Germany at 5 centers with room to grow north is your problem as much as mine. Coordinate with me now or watch Germany consolidate.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy — good. A TRI pressing toward BUD or VIE is exactly right. I am moving A BUR to MUN and A SPA to GAS this spring — Germany will be under direct pressure and cannot assist Austria. Hold your commitment to stay out of MAR and PIE and I hold mine to stay out of your sphere. Austria pinned in the Balkans by you while I squeeze Germany from the west is the correct 1902 posture for both of us. Execute your Adriatic push — I will not interfere.'}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Germany — you did not respond last round, so I am acting on the assumption of hostility. A BUR moves to MUN this spring. This is not negotiable at this point — the window for a boundary agreement closed when you stayed silent. If you want to stop the bleeding in 1903, I am open to terms then. For now, England is pressing from the north and France from the west — you cannot hold both.'}]
--------------
ENG
[{'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, I'm with you on containing France. Here are my specific commitments this spring: F BEL holds in place to secure our shared border and deny France any northern advance. F NWY moves to NTH to give me flexibility and naval dominance. A YOR moves to LON to free up positioning. I will NOT move F BEL into HOL - that remains yours. In return, I need your assurance that A HOL does NOT move toward BEL. Push A RUH into BUR and let's see France squeezed from both sides. If you take BUR this spring, I'll be positioned to support a drive toward PAR in the fall. Agreed?"}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'France, I hear your concerns about Germany, and I share them to a degree - but I must be honest with you: Germany has approached me with a similar anti-France proposal, and I am playing a careful game. My actual intention this spring is to hold F BEL defensively and move F NWY to NTH for naval positioning. I will NOT actively support Germany against you. However, I cannot commit F BEL to support HOL against Germany either - that would expose me. What I can offer: if Germany moves aggressively on BEL, I will defend it and that protects your northern flank too. Keep A BUR pressing MUN - a weakened Germany serves us both.'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, confirmed - Sweden is yours, no objection from London. F BOT to SWE is clean and I will not interfere. F NWY will move to NTH this spring, keeping well clear of your northern operations. I'd ask one thing in return: keep me informed if Austria or Turkey makes moves that could destabilize the east rapidly. A balanced east serves British interests as much as yours."}]
--------------
RUS
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Comrade, let us finalize our coordination precisely. My moves this spring: A UKR - WAR (to retake my home center from Austria), F RUM supports A UKR if needed OR F RUM - BUL if you can vacate BUL first. I need you to move A BUL - SER to pressure Austria from the south and free BUL for my fleet. F BLA holds to secure our sea. A SEV holds to protect home. If you move A BUL to SER, I move F RUM to BUL - we both gain and Austria is squeezed from two directions simultaneously. This is the moment to strike Austria hard. Confirm A BUL - SER and I execute F RUM - BUL.'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, your offer is rejected. You propose I surrender RUM - a center I hold and fought for - in exchange for WAR which is already mine by right. This is not a negotiation, it is extortion. I am taking WAR back by force this spring. Your threat to coordinate with Turkey against me is hollow - Turkey is my ally and will not turn against me for your benefit. Vacate WAR peacefully and I will not press further into your territory. Resist and I will coordinate with Turkey to dismantle your Balkan position entirely. The choice is yours, but my army moves to WAR regardless.'}, {'recipients': ['ENG', 'GER'], 'body': 'Confirmed: F BOT moves to SWE this spring - Sweden is mine as agreed with England. Germany, I am pressing Austria hard on WAR this turn - expect Austria to be fully occupied on their eastern front, giving you freedom in the west. A strong Russia-Germany axis dividing Europe is exactly the right long-term arrangement. Keep France and England busy in the west while I handle Austria and Turkey in the east. No conflicts between us this season.'}]
--------------
GER
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "England, let's lock in specific moves. I will order A RUH - BUR this spring to strike directly at France's heartland. A HOL holds to secure our northern flank. F DEN moves to NTH to support your naval operations. I need you to move F BEL to support my A RUH - BUR, or at minimum hold BEL to prevent France retreating there. If we coordinate this correctly, I take BUR this spring and we can split France's remaining centers between us next fall - you take PAR and the Atlantic ports, I take MAR and the south. France's offer of a 'buffer' is stalling tactics - they have 5 centers and will only grow stronger if we hesitate. Strike now while they're exposed. Confirm F BEL supports A RUH - BUR."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, your explanation of the MUN 'accident' is noted but unconvincing - armies do not accidentally march into enemy home centers. However, I am a pragmatic man. If you want peace, here are my terms: A BUR retreats to PAR or GAS immediately this spring, and France acknowledges HOL and BEL as German and English spheres respectively. In return I will not advance into BUR this season. But if A BUR remains in BUR threatening MUN, I will treat it as continued aggression and act accordingly with England's full cooperation. You have one move to demonstrate good faith."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, understood on SWE - I have no objection to your fleet moving there, England may have views but that is between you and them. I am moving west against France this spring. One request: if Austria moves any units toward Silesia or Bohemia while I am engaged westward, I would appreciate a warning. Our mutual interest in a stable central Europe depends on Austria staying focused on the Balkans and not opportunistically stabbing northward. Keep pressing them in the east and we both prosper.'}]
--------------
TUR
[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Comrade, let us be precise for this spring. I will move A BUL to GRE to secure that center, and F BLA will hold in the Black Sea to maintain our dominance there. I strongly recommend you move F RUM to hold or advance toward SEV while A UKR pushes to WAR to reclaim your home center from Austria - that is your priority target. A SEV can support F RUM or move to ARM. Austria is proposing I support A SER into RUM, which I am refusing - I will not betray our alliance. Hold RUM, take WAR back, and we squeeze Austria from both sides. Confirm you are not moving F RUM to BUL as that would conflict with my A BUL position.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, confirmed - I am moving A BUL to GRE this spring. Your F TUN moving to ION is excellent and keeps Austria's F ALB pinned. I also have F BLA holding in the Black Sea. Austria is trying to bribe me into supporting A SER into RUM, but I am refusing - Russia is my ally and Austria is the threat. With you pressing from the Adriatic and me taking GRE, Austria's southern position collapses. Let's continue this coordination into summer - after GRE, I can push toward SER while you pressure TRI. This is the moment to break Austrian power in the Balkans."}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, I have considered your proposal carefully, but I cannot support A SER into RUM - Russia is my ally and I will not betray that relationship for a single center. However, I am taking GRE this spring with A BUL, and I have no designs on SER itself. If you keep F ALB out of the Aegean and focus entirely on your northern conflict with Russia, we need not be enemies. The choice is yours: fight me in the south while Russia presses from the north, or accept Turkish dominance of GRE and concentrate your forces where they matter.'}]
--------------
AUT
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Turkey, I accept your terms: Greece is yours, and I will keep F ALB out of Greek waters. My moves this spring: F ALB to ADR (away from your sphere), A SER holds, A WAR to GAL. In return, I need one concrete action from you: A BUL supports A SER into RUM, or at minimum A BUL moves to RUM directly to contest Russia. Russia holds both RUM and is pushing into WAR - they are the dominant threat to both of us. If we coordinate now against Russia, we both grow. If we let Russia consolidate, they will be unstoppable. This is the moment to act together. Confirm A BUL moves against RUM and we have a deal.'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, your ultimatum is noted. Here is my counter: I will move A WAR to GAL this spring, vacating Warsaw voluntarily - you can retake it uncontested. However, I will NOT simply hand you RUM as well. You already hold RUM, SEV, MOS, STP - four centers to my four. If you push into WAR while keeping RUM, you grow to five while I shrink to three. That is unacceptable. My offer stands: vacate RUM (move F RUM to SEV or BUL), I take RUM, you retake WAR, and we maintain parity and peace. If you refuse and attack, I will coordinate with Turkey and Italy against you immediately - I have already opened those discussions. The choice is yours.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, I appreciate your cooperative stance. To be specific about my moves: A WAR to GAL, A SER holds, F ALB to ADR. I am NOT moving on Trieste or any Italian center - you have my word. Regarding your plan to move A TRI toward VIE or TYR: I must ask you to reconsider - moving toward VIE threatens my home center and would force me to respond defensively, damaging our relationship. Instead, keep A TRI in place or move it toward VEN to free up your forces. On Germany: I agree they are growing fast, but I cannot reach them easily from my position. Focus your pressure on Germany from the south while I handle the Balkans, and we both benefit. Let's not accidentally clash."}]
