GER
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "The situation is clear: France occupies MUN with A MUN and has A GAS threatening further. I intend to retake MUN this fall - A BUR moves to MUN. I need you to hold F BEL firm and consider moving A LON to support pressure on France from the north. If you can push toward PAR or support my western flank, we can crack France open together. I'll keep A HOL in place to reassure you on HOL. What can you commit to against France this fall?"}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'You sit in MY Munich with MY army. This is not a negotiating position - this is an occupation of German soil. Withdraw A MUN back to BUR immediately and we can discuss terms. If you refuse, I will retake MUN by force and you will find yourself fighting on two fronts. I have no interest in prolonged war with France if you respect German territory, but I will not tolerate this provocation. Your choice.'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'France has occupied Munich - a direct act of aggression against Germany. I am moving to retake it this fall. I want to confirm our non-aggression holds firm - I have no eastern ambitions and need my units focused west. In return, I will not contest SWE and will support your position against Austria if needed. Are we aligned for the foreseeable future?'}]
--------------
ENG
[{'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Germany, the situation is clear: France has taken MUN and is growing dangerously strong at 5 centers with Atlantic access. I propose we coordinate directly this fall. I will move F BEL to HOL, taking it from you - but in exchange, I want you to support A BUR into MUN to retake it from France, and we split the spoils. Alternatively, if you prefer I support your A HOL to hold while you push BUR into MUN, I can do that too. Either way, France must be checked. What do you propose? I need a specific commitment from you this turn.'}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, you've taken MUN which is impressive, but Germany will not let that stand - they will push BUR into MUN this fall with everything they have. I can help you hold MUN if you give me something concrete: promise me you will not contest HOL or move into the Channel, and I will use F BEL to support your A MUN against German pressure. A strong France holding MUN weakens Germany considerably, which serves both our interests. What are your planned moves this fall?"}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, you've secured SWE and RUM - well played. I want to ensure we maintain our northern understanding. I have F NWY and you have F SWE - let's keep this border peaceful. I'm focused on the continent right now. Are you planning to push south toward TUR or west? I'd like to coordinate so we don't accidentally step on each other's interests in Scandinavia."}]
--------------
RUS
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Comrade, our alliance has served us both well. This fall I intend: F RUM moves to BUL (now that your A BUL has moved to GRE, the center is open - I'm taking it), A WAR holds to secure my home center, F SWE holds, A SEV holds. I need your confirmation that A BUL did indeed move to GRE and BUL is vacant. If so, F RUM to BUL is clean. I also want to coordinate our next moves against Austria - your A CON and my forces can squeeze them from multiple directions. What are your intentions this fall? Let's divide Austria's centers between us."}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, your position is deteriorating rapidly. Italy has taken BUD, I hold WAR, and Turkey presses from the south. I offer you one chance at a negotiated arrangement: withdraw A GAL back to VIE and I will not press further into your home centers this turn. Refuse, and I coordinate with Italy and Turkey to eliminate you entirely. Your choice - cooperation or annihilation. I am a practical man and prefer a living Austria as a buffer, but only if you stop threatening my interests.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, you hold BUD which is excellent. I hold WAR. Together we can dismember Austria completely - you take VIE and TRI, I take GAL. Austria has A SER, F ALB, and A GAL left - they are weak. Propose we coordinate: your A BUD moves to VIE, I move A WAR to GAL. Austria collapses. What are your intentions this fall and can we formalize this cooperation?'}]
--------------
ITA
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Excellent work this spring - we've both positioned well. I now hold BUD with my army, and my F ION dominates the Ionian. I propose we coordinate directly against Austria this fall: I will move A BUD to either VIE or SER, and F ION can move to AEG or support your push toward GRE. Austria's F ALB is isolated and vulnerable - if you move A BUL to GRE and I support from ION, we can crack them open. What are your intended moves? Let's divide the Balkans between us - I take VIE and BUD, you take GRE and BUL, and we squeeze Austria out of existence."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "The spring went well for both of us - you're in MUN, I'm in BUD. Austria is being squeezed from multiple directions. This fall I intend to push A BUD toward VIE or hold to consolidate, while F ION threatens the eastern Mediterranean. I need you to maintain pressure on Austria from MUN - can you move A MUN toward VIE or BOH to prevent Austria from reinforcing? If we coordinate, Austria collapses within two seasons and we both gain. What are your fall intentions?"}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, I'll be direct: I hold BUD and have no intention of returning it. However, I have no interest in destroying you entirely - a weakened Austria is more useful to me than a dead one. If you cede BUD formally and focus your forces on Russia (who holds RUM and WAR), I will support your eastern ambitions and not press further into VIE. Russia is the real threat to both of us. Consider: A GAL can push into WAR, F RUM is a Russian asset threatening your flank. Work with me against Russia and I'll stabilize your position."}]
--------------
TUR
[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, the situation is clear: Austria holds SER with an army, has a fleet in ALB threatening Greece, and a unit in GAL threatening your position. I propose we coordinate directly this fall. I will move A BUL to GRE (finally taking it uncontested since AUT's F ALB moved to ADR last spring). More importantly, I want to discuss RUM - you hold it with F RUM, but Austria's A GAL is a threat. If you move F RUM to support against Austria, I can position A BUL to threaten SER next spring. Let's divide the Balkans: I take GRE, you keep RUM, we jointly pressure Austria. What are your specific moves this fall?"}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, our coordination worked well last spring - you moved F TUN to ION as agreed. Now let's continue. I am moving A BUL to GRE this fall - with your F ION in position, AUT cannot contest it. Austria is the common threat: they hold SER, TRI (your home!), and have been aggressive in the Balkans. I propose we both pressure Austria - you push from BUD toward VIE or TRI, I take GRE and threaten SER. Austria cannot defend on two fronts. What are your intended moves this fall? I want to ensure we don't interfere with each other."}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, I am taking Greece this fall - A BUL to GRE. I have no interest in SER or RUM at this time. However, I notice Italy has taken BUD and is positioned aggressively against you. I could be persuaded to support your interests in the Balkans if you formally concede Greece to my sphere and keep F ALB away from the Aegean. Otherwise, I will coordinate with Italy and Russia against you. The choice is yours - make me an offer.'}]
--------------
AUT
[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, let's be direct: you took TRI and BUD, and I'm now squeezed from all sides. I have no interest in fighting you - that only benefits Russia and Turkey. I propose a clean division: you keep TRI and I keep BUD. I will move A GAL to BUD to reclaim it this fall - if you move A BUD elsewhere (say, toward RUM or SER), we avoid a clash and both gain. Russia holds RUM and WAR threatens my north; Turkey holds BUL and threatens my south. We have a common interest in not letting Russia dominate the east. I can offer you support into GRE or RUM if we coordinate. What do you say?"}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, the situation has clarified considerably. Italy has seized BUD and TRI - they are now the dominant Balkan power, not me. I am fighting for survival against Italy from the west, Turkey from the south, and your pressure from the north. I propose a genuine ceasefire: I will not contest WAR or RUM this turn. In exchange, I ask you to hold F RUM in place and not advance on GAL. Italy is the real threat to both of us in the Balkans - A BUD gives them a foothold that threatens both our interests. Consider: a coordinated AUT-RUS push against Italy benefits us both far more than continuing to grind each other down.'}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, Italy now occupies BUD and TRI - they have 5 centers and are the strongest power in the Balkans. This threatens you as much as me. I propose we set aside our rivalry over GRE temporarily: I will move F ALB to GRE this fall if you support it, or we can coordinate A SER to BUL while you take GRE. Either way, we should be focused on containing Italy, not fighting each other. What specific moves are you planning this fall? Let's find an arrangement that benefits us both."}]
