FRA
[{'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Germany, you now hold BUR and I hold MUN. This is a stalemate that benefits neither of us while England consolidates in the north and Austria grows unchecked in the east. I am prepared to offer you a clean partition: I keep MUN and push east toward BOH and SIL, you take BEL from England and consolidate the north. We both gain more from coordinating against England and Austria than from grinding against each other on the Rhine. If you reject this, I will hold MUN and support it from GAS — you will not retake it without English help, and England will extract a price for that help. The offer is on the table for this season only.'}, {'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "England, France now holds MUN and GER holds BUR — the German position is cracking. I intend to press east into BOH or BER this fall. This is the moment to coordinate: if you move F BEL toward HOL or press GER from the north, we split Germany between us and both gain centers. I am not moving against BEL or the Channel — my fleet is in POR and my armies are pointed east. What I need from you is confirmation you will not support GER's attempt to retake MUN. In return I will stay clear of BEL and NTH. Specific ask: hold BEL or move toward HOL, do not support GER into BUR or MUN."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, your move into BUD is excellent — Austria is now squeezed between you and Russia. I am holding MUN and pressing deeper into Germany this fall. I need you to continue pinning Austria so they cannot reinforce the German theater. Specific coordination: keep A BUD in place or push toward VIE, and if F ION can threaten the Adriatic that keeps Austria's fleet options closed. I will stay entirely out of your sphere — MAR, PIE, LYO are yours. The western and central board is splitting cleanly between us. What is your intended move for F1902?"}]
INFO:main:Negotiation sub-round 2/2
--------------
GER
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "England, I reject your proposal to take HOL - that is a non-starter and you know it. Here is what I will do: A BUR moves to MUN to retake my home center. A HOL holds. F DEN moves to support or threatens SWE. I need you to hold F BEL firm and NOT move to HOL - that is the price of our cooperation. If you move on HOL while I'm fighting France, our alliance ends immediately and I will make accommodations with France against you. Hold BEL, let me retake MUN, and we coordinate against France together next season from a position of strength. That is the deal."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'France, your offer is insulting. You want me to accept the permanent loss of Munich - a German home center - in exchange for attacking England? I will retake MUN by force this fall. A BUR moves to MUN. If you hold MUN with support from GAS, you will find yourself in a grinding war of attrition you cannot win while England presses from the north. Withdraw now and I will consider a ceasefire on the Rhine. This is your final warning.'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, France is attempting to permanently occupy Munich and is offering me a fantasy deal to distract me. I am retaking MUN this fall - A BUR to MUN. Our non-aggression stands firm and I appreciate your confirmation. Austria is stretched thin with your pressure from the east - keep it up. Once France is contained, Germany and Russia together can dominate the board. Stay the course.'}]
--------------
AUT
[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, I accept your framing - Russia is the primary threat. Here is my concrete proposal: I will move A GAL to BUD to reclaim it (you should move A BUD to RUM to take that center from Russia - F RUM is exposed and you can take it). F ALB moves to GRE. A SER holds. This way you gain RUM, I regain BUD, and we both expand at Russia's expense. I will not move on TRI or VEN. This is a genuine offer - let's execute it together this fall."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, I hear your ultimatum but consider the reality: Italy holds BUD and TRI with 5 centers - they are the dominant power now, not me. I am moving A GAL to BUD to reclaim my home center from Italy. I am NOT moving on WAR or RUM this turn. F RUM is actually vulnerable to Italian A BUD - you should consider whether Italy is truly your ally or simply using you. I propose we both focus on containing Italy: hold F RUM where it is, and I will not threaten your positions. A living Austria as a buffer serves you better than an Italian-dominated Balkans.'}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, agreed - Greece is yours, I concede it formally. A BUL to GRE is fine by me. In exchange, I ask one thing: do not support Italy against me. I am moving A GAL to BUD to reclaim my home center from Italy. F ALB will move to GRE as well - if you're already moving A BUL there we'll bounce, but that's acceptable to me as it keeps the fleet away from your sphere. The real threat is Italy at 5 centers. Stay neutral between me and Italy this fall and I will formally recognize your sphere over GRE and BUL."}]
--------------
ITA
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Confirmed: I will move F ION to AEG this fall to support your A BUL to GRE - Austria's F ALB cannot stop both of us. My A BUD will push to VIE to strike Austria's heartland. This is the killing blow: you take GRE, I take VIE, Austria is finished. Do not let Austria's F ALB escape to ADR - if it retreats there it threatens my position. Move A CON toward SMY or hold to free up your forces for the Balkan push. We are aligned - execute."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, I accept your proposal in principle - Austria must be dismembered. I will push A BUD toward VIE this fall while you press A WAR into GAL. However, I want clarity on RUM: that fleet concerns me as it borders my sphere of influence in the Balkans. I propose you keep F RUM focused on BUL or the Black Sea, not the Adriatic or Balkan interior. If we coordinate cleanly - you take GAL and WAR, I take VIE and BUD - Austria collapses by 1903 and we can discuss a stable border. Agreed?'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, I appreciate your directness but I cannot accept your terms. BUD is mine and VIE is my next objective - this is the reality of your strategic position. However, I offer you this: if you move A SER to hold and A GAL to support against Russia, I will not press into TRI this fall. Your survival depends on choosing your battles - fight Russia in the east, not me in the west. A GAL pushing into RUM would actually serve both our interests and buy you time. The alternative is a three-front collapse.'}]
--------------
RUS
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Confirmed - my moves this fall: F RUM moves to BUL (taking the vacant center after your A BUL moves to GRE), A WAR holds, F SWE holds, A SEV holds. This gives me BUL and secures WAR. Next spring I propose: A WAR to GAL, F BUL supports or moves toward SER, your forces press from CON/GRE toward SER and VIE. Austria is finished. After Austria falls, we divide cleanly - you take SER, GRE, and the Adriatic coast; I take GAL, VIE, and BUD. This is the most efficient path to dominance for both of us. Confirm your A BUL is indeed moving to GRE this fall so I can execute F RUM - BUL without conflict.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, I am moving A WAR to GAL this fall and F RUM to BUL - Austria will be squeezed from all sides. Your A BUD is perfectly positioned to take VIE next spring with my support from GAL. I propose we formalize: you take VIE and TRI (your home centers), I take GAL and WAR (my home centers). Austria is eliminated and we both grow. I have no interest in your Adriatic or Italian sphere - my focus is the Balkans and eastern Europe. Confirm you are pressing Austria this fall and we can coordinate the killing blow next spring.'}, {'recipients': ['ENG', 'GER'], 'body': "England, Germany - our northern arrangement remains solid. I am focused entirely on Austria and the Balkans this fall. F SWE holds, no moves toward Scandinavia or the west from me. Germany, your non-aggression with me is confirmed - retake Munich from France, I have no interest in your western affairs. England, NWY is yours, SWE is mine, let's keep that border clean indefinitely. I will not interfere in your contest with France or Germany. We all benefit from stability in the north while I handle the eastern situation."}]
--------------
TUR
[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, I must be direct with you: A BUL did NOT move to GRE last spring - it bounced with AUT's F ALB. BUL is still occupied by my army. F RUM moving to BUL would be moving into my occupied territory and I will not allow it. This would be an act of aggression against our alliance. My moves this fall: A BUL to GRE (finally uncontested since AUT's F ALB is now in ALB not GRE), F BLA holds, A CON moves to SMY. BUL will be vacant after I move to GRE - but I need your commitment that F RUM stays in RUM and does not take BUL. BUL is my center and I intend to keep it. In exchange, I will support your position against Austria - A BUL can threaten SER next spring. Do not move F RUM to BUL or our alliance ends immediately."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, confirmed: I am moving A BUL to GRE this fall, F BLA holds, A CON to SMY. Your F ION in the Ionian is perfect - if you move to AEG it supports my GRE move and we lock down the eastern Med together. On Austria: I agree they are the target. You push A BUD toward VIE, I take GRE and will threaten SER next spring. However, watch Russia - they just told me they intend to move F RUM into BUL (my center!) which suggests they are expanding aggressively westward. Russia with 5+ centers is as dangerous as Austria. Let's eliminate Austria first, then reassess. Confirm your moves so we don't interfere."}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, your offer is too little too late. Italy holds BUD and threatens VIE - you are already losing. I am taking GRE this fall regardless. However, I will offer you this: I have no interest in SER right now, and I can tell you that Russia intends to move F RUM aggressively this fall. If you want to survive, you need to focus on Italy in BUD, not contest me in Greece. Keep F ALB away from GRE and A SER where it is, and I will not coordinate with Italy against you this phase. That is the best offer you will get from me.'}]
--------------
ENG
[{'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, I'm with you against France. My orders this fall: F BEL moves to HOL (taking it from you, but this is the price for my active participation), and F NWY moves to NTH to dominate the seas. In exchange, I need you to push A BUR into MUN to retake it from France, and hold A HOL to support my move if needed. Yes, you lose HOL temporarily, but you gain MUN back and we crack France open together. I will not support France's position in MUN - that is my firm commitment. France is the greater threat at 5 centers with Atlantic ports. Let's coordinate and divide their territory."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, I've considered your proposal carefully. I will hold F BEL in place this fall and will not actively support Germany's push into BUR or MUN - you have my word on that. However, I cannot move F BEL toward HOL as that would antagonize Germany unnecessarily and expose my flank. Hold MUN if you can, push east as you plan, and keep your forces away from BEL and the Channel as promised. We both benefit from a weakened Germany, but I must maintain my position carefully. Stay the course and we'll both profit."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, glad we're aligned in the north. I'm keeping F NWY in place or moving to NTH for naval positioning - no threat to SWE or STP from me. Focus your energies south against Turkey and Romania; that's where your growth lies. I'll manage the North Sea and Scandinavia from my side. Let's keep this border quiet and both expand in our respective directions."}]
