FRA
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "England, my moves this fall: A MUN holds, A GAS moves to BUR to support MUN, F POR moves to MAO. I am not touching HOL, BEL, or the Channel — my entire effort is eastward into Germany. What I need from you is exactly what you offered: F BEL supports A MUN against GER's A BUR push. If you deliver that support, MUN holds and GER loses their best offensive unit's tempo. In return I will stay clear of HOL and NTH for the remainder of 1902. This is a clean exchange — confirm you will execute F BEL S A MUN."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, my fall plan: A MUN holds, A GAS to BUR to reinforce the German front, F POR to MAO. I cannot push A MUN toward BOH or VIE this season — I need it to hold against GER's counterattack. What I need from you is continued pressure on Austria: push A BUD toward VIE if you can, or hold and threaten. Austria reinforcing the German theater is the one scenario that breaks our coordination. Keep them pinned and we both gain centers by year end."}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, your ultimatum changes nothing. A MUN holds, supported from GAS via BUR. You will not retake it this season without English help, and England has already told me they will not provide it. The offer I made last round stands: partition the board, coordinate against England and Austria, and both of us grow. If you push BUR into MUN unsupported, you lose the unit's tempo and I advance into BER next spring. The rational move is negotiation, not a failed assault."}]
