[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Excellent work last fall - Austria is crippled and we hold strong positions. I now have F AEG and A VIE. My plan this spring: F AEG moves to CON or supports your units, A VIE pushes to BUD to finish Austria. I propose we coordinate to eliminate Austria entirely this year - you take BUL/GRE/SER, I take BUD and VIE. Once Austria is gone we can discuss a formal division of the Balkans. What are your intended moves? I want to ensure we don't clash in the Aegean or Balkans."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Austria is nearly finished - A VIE is mine and I intend to push to BUD this spring. I suggest you move A WAR to GAL to pressure BUD from the north, which combined with my A VIE-BUD should eliminate Austria's last resistance. In return I'll stay out of GAL and RUM - those are your sphere. Let's coordinate to finish Austria quickly before Turkey grows too powerful in the Balkans. What are your spring intentions?"}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, you hold MUN and GAS - impressive position. Austria is nearly dead; I'm finishing them this spring with A VIE-BUD. I want to ensure we don't have friction - I have no interest in MUN or your western territories. My focus is the Balkans and eastern Mediterranean. Germany looks vulnerable with only 4 centers and BUR in your hands. If you're considering pushing east, I won't interfere. What are your plans this season?"}]
