GER
[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Comrade, the situation demands we coordinate closely. France has stolen Munich and England is attempting to seize Holland - I am surrounded by opportunists. I intend to push A BUR into MUN to retake my home center, and I need to know Russia's intentions regarding Sweden and the north. I propose we maintain our non-aggression pact firmly - I have no eastern ambitions and need my full strength westward. If you can pressure England from the north (SWE toward NTH or NWY), you would be doing both of us a great service. What can we arrange?"}, {'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'England, let us be direct: you attempted to take Holland last season and failed. I held it. Now we both face a France that has 6 centers and is growing. My A BUR will push into MUN this spring to retake my home center. I propose a genuine ceasefire - HOL remains German, BEL remains English, and we coordinate against France together. I can move A BUR into MUN while you press F BEL toward PIC or support an attack on PAR. France is the common threat. If you continue pressing HOL, you hand France the victory. What specific moves can you commit to against France this turn?'}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'France, you have overplayed your hand. Munich is German soil and I am coming to take it back. A BUR moves to MUN this spring - your occupation ends now. If you wish to avoid a prolonged war that exhausts us both while England and Russia grow fat, then withdraw from MUN voluntarily and we can discuss a genuine partition of western Europe. Otherwise, expect relentless pressure until your armies are driven back to Paris. The choice is yours, but know that I am fully committed to this fight.'}]
--------------
TUR
[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Your attempt to steal BUL last fall was noted and blocked. F RUM is sitting in MY supply center territory and I have not forgotten your explicit statement that you would take BUL regardless of our agreement. Consider this a final warning: F RUM must retreat to SEV or BUD this spring, or I will treat Russia as a hostile power and coordinate with ITA and AUT to eliminate your southern presence entirely. I am willing to restore our working relationship if you demonstrate good faith by moving F RUM away from my sphere. What is your response?'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "The situation has clarified considerably. Russia attempted to steal BUL last fall - I blocked it by holding A BUL. Your F AEG is now perfectly positioned to support my push into GRE this spring. I propose: A BUL moves to GRE with F AEG support, while F RUM is pressured by my fleet. AUT holds GRE with F GRE but is weak - with your support from AEG we take it cleanly. In exchange, I will support your continued pressure on AUT's remaining centers. Russia is now my primary threat and I need to secure GRE before turning north. Are you with me on A BUL-GRE supported by F AEG?"}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, we have both been squeezed by opportunistic neighbors - Italy has taken VIE and threatens your remaining centers, while Russia sits in RUM adjacent to both of us. I propose a pragmatic arrangement: I will not contest SER if you withdraw F GRE to allow me to take it uncontested. In return, I will support your efforts to recover BUD from Italy. Russia in RUM is a shared problem - if you move A BUD toward GAL to pressure Russia, I can threaten from the south with F RUM. Let us stop bouncing each other in GRE and focus on real threats.'}]
--------------
RUS
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'I must be direct with you: I took BUL last fall when you vacated it. I understand this damages our relationship, but I need supply centers to remain competitive. Here is my proposal going forward: I will not move into CON, SMY, or ANK - your home centers are safe from me. I propose we redirect our cooperation against Austria, who sits at BUD and SER with only 3 centers but is vulnerable. My A WAR can move to GAL, your A BUL can press SER, and we divide the Balkans. I offer you GRE and SER while I take RUM back and GAL. This is more valuable than fighting each other. What do you say?'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, you hold VIE and are pressing Austria hard - excellent work. I propose direct coordination: I will move A WAR to GAL this spring, threatening BUD from the north. You press from VIE toward BUD or TRI. Austria cannot defend on two fronts simultaneously. If we coordinate, we eliminate Austria within two turns and divide their centers - I take BUD and GAL, you keep VIE, TRI, and SER. This gives us both the supply centers we need to compete with the western powers who are growing dangerously. France has 6 centers already. Confirm your moves and let's act together."}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, France has 6 centers and is the dominant western power - MUN, SPA, POR, BRE, MAR, PAR. You need to retake MUN urgently. I have no designs on your territory and remain committed to our non-aggression arrangement. My focus is entirely on Austria and the Balkans. I would ask only that you keep pressure on France from BUR and HOL so they cannot expand eastward. A strong Germany is in Russia's interest as a counterweight to French dominance. What is your plan for retaking MUN?"}]
