FRA
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'MUN held. Germany is cracked open. My intended moves this season: A MUN - BER, A GAS - BUR (to hold the corridor), F MAO holds or moves to NAF depending on your posture. I need to know if you will move F BEL toward HOL or at minimum hold it to prevent GER from reinforcing BER. If you take HOL this season while I take BER, Germany is finished — two home centers gone, no recovery path. I am not asking you to fight my war; I am offering you HOL on a plate while I absorb BER. The promise I made about HOL expires at year end and I am offering you first claim on it now. What are your moves?'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'France holds MUN, Germany is exposed. I am pushing A MUN - BER this season to crack their home centers. Your position at VIE is excellent — if you can press toward BOH or TYR, you pin any German retreat and we squeeze from both sides. Austria is your primary target and I will not interfere in the east. What is your plan for VIE and BUD this season? I want to coordinate so we are not working at cross purposes.'}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Germany, you have one move left before this becomes irreversible. France holds MUN and is moving on BER. England is positioned at BEL and will not defend you. Italy sits in VIE. You are surrounded. The only path that preserves any German centers is an immediate arrangement: cede BER to France in exchange for a ceasefire and French support against England in the north. I have no interest in your destruction if you cooperate — I have every interest in finishing you quickly if you resist. This offer does not survive the season.'}]
