ENG
[{'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "I understand tensions ran high last year over HOL - my F BEL bounced attempting to take it, which I'll admit was opportunistic on my part. The situation has changed: France now holds MUN and has a strong Atlantic position with F MAO threatening your western flank. I propose we coordinate properly this spring: I will move F NTH to support F BEL into HOL, giving me HOL while you focus A BUR and A HOL on retaking MUN from France. This is a clean division - I get HOL, you get MUN back. France at 6 centers is a greater threat to both of us than any dispute between us. What say you?"}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, you've had a strong run - MUN is impressive. But I must be direct: Germany is furious and will throw everything at retaking MUN this spring. I have F BEL and F NTH positioned in the north. I'm willing to stay neutral in the Franco-German fight IF you acknowledge my claim to HOL - I intend to move on it this turn regardless. A France that holds MUN and lets me take HOL is a France I can work with long-term. The alternative is I coordinate with Germany against you. Your choice - respond with your intentions."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, our northern arrangement has held well - NWY mine, SWE yours. I want to maintain that stability. My focus this spring is on HOL and the continental balance. I have no designs on SWE or STP. I'd ask only that you keep F SWE out of NTH - that sea is mine to manage. In return, I'll stay out of your Baltic affairs entirely. Are we agreed on continued northern non-interference?"}]
