AUT
[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Vienna, we need to talk frankly. You hold VIE and BUD - two of my home centers. I hold SER and GRE. I have no path to survival unless we reach an accommodation. I propose this: I will not contest VIE or TRI this turn. In exchange, I ask you to move A VIE away from BUD and allow me to retake BUD with A SER. You keep VIE and TRI, I keep BUD, SER, GRE - we stabilize the front and both turn our attention to the real threats: France is at 6 centers, Russia at 5, Turkey at 5. If you eliminate me, you gain 3 centers but face those giants alone. If we stabilize, I become a useful buffer and ally. What do you want from me to make this work?'}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Turkey, I want to formalize our understanding. I concede GRE to your sphere - F GRE will move to ION or ALB this turn, vacating the territory for you. In exchange, I need your active support: specifically, can F RUM support A SER into BUL, or can A BUL move elsewhere to allow me breathing room? Italy is the dominant threat with 6 centers - they threaten both of us eventually. A coordinated Austria-Turkey front against Italian expansion in the Balkans serves us both. I am offering you GRE freely. What can you offer me in return?'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, I understand we have been at odds, but consider the strategic reality: Italy now holds VIE and BUD with 6 centers - they are the dominant power and a direct threat to both of us. I propose a temporary ceasefire: I will not contest GAL or RUM this turn if you do not press into my remaining centers. Let us both focus on containing Italy and France. A dead Austria benefits only Italy and Turkey. A living Austria as a buffer serves Russian interests. What specific arrangement would satisfy you this season?'}]
