[{'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, your offer is compelling and I'm moving on it. My orders this spring: F NTH supports F BEL into HOL, and F BEL moves to HOL. This takes HOL from Germany while you push A MUN to BER. Germany loses two home centers simultaneously - that's a knockout blow. I will NOT support Germany against you in any way. After this turn, we should discuss dividing the German carcass: I take HOL and KIE via sea, you hold BER and MUN. Coordinate your A GAS to BUR to hold the corridor and prevent any German counterattack. Let's finish this."}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, I've considered your proposal carefully, but France is offering me HOL in exchange for neutrality while they take BER - I'd be a fool to refuse a free center. My advice: abandon MUN and pull back to defend BER and KIE before France overruns you. If you want to survive, you need to make concessions to someone. I'm willing to discuss a future arrangement once the dust settles, but right now France has the momentum and I intend to profit from it. Nothing personal - this is simply the balance of power at work."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, confirming our northern arrangement holds - NWY mine, SWE yours, no interference from either side. My focus is entirely on HOL this turn. I expect Germany will be significantly weakened after this spring, which opens interesting possibilities for both of us. Keep your F SWE out of NTH and I'll stay out of the Baltic entirely. Once Germany is reduced, we should talk about coordinating against whoever emerges as the dominant continental power."}]
--------------
GER
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'England, your offer is rejected. You want HOL while I bleed against France - that is not partnership, that is parasitism. I am holding HOL with A HOL and pushing A BUR into MUN. If you move F NTH to support F BEL into HOL, you will bounce against my army and waste your move while France consolidates. The smart play for you is F NTH toward NWY or pressing F BEL toward PIC to threaten PAR. France at 6 centers destroys us both. I am fighting France - join me properly or watch France win this game while you squabble over HOL.'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, my moves this spring: A BUR - MUN to retake my home center, A HOL holds to deny England, F KIE moves to BAL or DEN for repositioning. France threatens to move on BER - if you can signal any pressure toward the north it would deter French adventurism eastward. I remain fully committed to our non-aggression arrangement. England is proving unreliable and opportunistic - they attempted to take HOL twice now. A strong Germany-Russia axis is the only counterweight to French dominance. I will keep you informed of all western developments.'}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, your ultimatum is laughable. Cede BER? You hold MUN with a single unsupported army while I have A BUR adjacent and A HOL threatening your western flank. I am taking MUN back this turn. Your 'move on BER' is a bluff - you have no units positioned for it. If you want to end this war, withdraw from MUN now and return to your natural borders. Otherwise I will grind you down season by season until Paris falls. England will not save you - they are too busy trying to steal from me to coordinate with you effectively."}]
