[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Confirmed - A BUL moves to GRE this spring with F AEG support. AUT has offered to vacate F GRE voluntarily, so this should succeed cleanly. My F RUM will move to BLA or hold to threaten Russia's position. I will not contest your moves toward BUD or VIE - Austria is yours to finish. After GRE falls to me, I propose we divide remaining Austrian centers: you take BUD, I take SER next phase. Russia is my primary concern now - they are trying to manipulate both of us. Do not let F AEG be redirected to CON as they suggested; I need that support on GRE. Our coordination is working - let's execute."}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, I accept your offer. Move F GRE to ION or ALB and I will take GRE with A BUL - no conflict between us. In return, I will not support Italian moves against your remaining centers this phase. F RUM will not be used against you. However, I cannot promise long-term protection from Italy - they are too strong and moving independently. Your best survival path is to hold BUD and SER tightly while I absorb GRE and redirect pressure toward Russia. We have a deal on GRE - honor it and I honor my neutrality toward you this phase.'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Your message is noted but your credibility is gone after explicitly stating you would take BUL regardless of our agreement. I blocked you last fall and I will block you again. F RUM sitting in my sphere is unacceptable - move it to SEV this spring or I will push F RUM to SEV myself and coordinate with ITA to eliminate your southern presence. I am taking GRE with A BUL this phase. If you want any future cooperation, demonstrate good faith by withdrawing F RUM to SEV immediately. Otherwise we are at war.'}]
