[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Confirmed - F AEG supports A BUL to GRE this spring. Austria's F GRE will be dislodged. My A VIE pushes to BUD to finish Austria entirely. Once GRE is yours and BUD is mine, we divide the Balkans cleanly: you hold GRE, BUL, RUM, SER; I hold BUD, VIE, TRI. Russia is the next threat - A WAR to GAL is their move and we must watch it carefully. After Austria falls, I propose we coordinate against Russia's southern expansion. Do not let F RUM threaten your position."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Coordination confirmed in principle, but I must be direct: I will not cede BUD to you - I am taking it with A VIE this spring and it becomes mine. You may have GAL and pressure from the north, but the Balkan centers go to Italy. Move A WAR to GAL to pressure Austria and prevent any counterattack - that is genuinely useful coordination. Turkey is your real threat in the south; F RUM sitting next to your sphere is dangerous. I suggest you focus on securing your southern flank against Turkey rather than competing with me over Austrian scraps.'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, your offer is noted but I cannot accept it. You have three units and three centers - if I allow you to retake BUD you simply rebuild and threaten me again. However, I will offer you this: if you order A SER to hold and F GRE to ION this spring, I will not press further than BUD this season and will consider a ceasefire. Resist and I coordinate with Turkey to eliminate you entirely within two turns. The choice is yours - a managed retreat or total elimination.'}]
