[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Excellent coordination last phase - GRE is now mine and Austria is crippled. I propose we continue our partnership: I will push A GRE into SER this fall while you hold your Balkan gains. Russia is my primary concern now - A SEV sits menacingly near my sphere and I intend to use F BLA to pressure them toward ARM or SEV. I suggest you hold VIE and VEN to consolidate while I handle the eastern front. What are your intentions this phase? I want to ensure we don't accidentally clash."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, your A SEV is dangerously close to my sphere and your credibility with me is destroyed after last year's BUL gambit. I am giving you one opportunity to demonstrate good faith: move A SEV to UKR or ARM, away from my centers. F BLA is positioned to move on SEV if you do not comply. I have no interest in war with you if you respect my sphere - RUM, BUL, GRE, and the Black Sea are mine. Acknowledge this and we can discuss cooperation against the western powers who are growing dangerously strong."}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, I honored my commitment and did not move on SER last phase. GRE is now mine as agreed. I propose we formalize a boundary: SER and BUD remain your sphere, I will not contest them this phase. However, I need you to keep F ION away from AEG - that sea is within my operational zone. Italy is the real threat to both of us now with 6 centers. Are you willing to coordinate against Italian overreach while I handle Russia in the east?'}]
