[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, we are both threatened by Turkey's aggression and Austria's desperation. My units are positioned: A GAL can move to BUD or RUM, A SEV holds in the south. I propose we coordinate directly - I will move A GAL to RUM to take that center from Turkey while you press BUD. This gives us both expansion without stepping on each other. Turkey at 5 centers with hostile intent toward both of us is the immediate danger. What are your specific moves this fall so we can avoid bouncing each other?"}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Turkey, I hold RUM and I intend to keep it - this is a defensive posture, not aggression. I have A GAL positioned and A SEV in the south. I am willing to discuss a new arrangement: I will not move into BUL or ANK if you accept RUM as mine and we redirect our energies against Italy, who now holds 6 centers including Vienna. Italy is the dominant threat to both of us. A RUS-TUR war benefits only Italy and Austria. Propose terms.'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, Italy occupies Vienna and threatens Budapest - you are nearly eliminated. I have A GAL adjacent to BUD and can support your A BUD to hold against Italy's pressure, or we can coordinate to retake VIE. My interest is in containing Italy's expansion, not destroying Austria. If you can hold BUD this fall, we can discuss a genuine anti-Italy arrangement. What are your orders this phase?"}]
