[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Excellent work last spring - TUR's A GRE is now secured and I hold VIE. Austria is crippled with only BUD, TRI (occupied by their own unit), and ION fleet. This fall I intend to move A VIE to BUD to eliminate Austria entirely, and F AEG can move to SMY or support your operations as needed. I propose we coordinate to finish Austria: I take BUD, you consolidate GRE and push toward RUM or BUL. Russia is growing fast with 5 centers - we should discuss containing them after Austria falls. What are your intended moves this fall?"}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Austria is nearly finished - I'm moving A VIE to BUD this fall to eliminate them. I note you have A GAL adjacent to BUD - please do NOT move A GAL to BUD as that would bounce my attack and save Austria. Hold GAL or move it elsewhere. In exchange, I have no designs on GAL or WAR. Once Austria is eliminated we should discuss dividing their remaining centers - I want BUD and TRI, you can have SER if you can reach it. Let's finish this together."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, you're doing well in the west - BER is a fine acquisition. Austria is nearly dead; I'm finishing them this fall. I want to flag that with 6 centers each, we are the two strongest powers and should avoid friction. I have no interest in MAR, PIE, or any French territory - my expansion is eastward into the Balkans and eastern Mediterranean. I'd welcome a formal non-aggression pact through 1905. What are your plans against Germany?"}]
