GER
[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "The situation has shifted dramatically in our favor. France's A BUR moved to MUN - taking my home center - but my A BUR captured PAR and my A HOL held against England's attempted seizure. I now sit in PAR with France scrambling. I need your continued support: keep F SWE out of the Baltic and away from BER, and I will ensure no German units threaten your western flank. Together we can crush France and contain England. Specifically: if you can pressure GAL toward SIL or keep Austria occupied, it prevents any flanking threat while I consolidate the west. What are your intentions this fall?"}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'You hold MUN, I hold PAR. We are at a stalemate that benefits neither of us while England grows fat in the north. I propose an immediate ceasefire: you return MUN, I return PAR, and we turn our combined strength against England who now holds BEL, NTH, NWY, EDI, LON, LVP - five centers and growing. England is the dominant power and will win if we continue bleeding each other. I am willing to discuss a formal partition of western Europe if you are serious about survival. Respond with your terms.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, you have made impressive gains - VIE, TRI, VEN, TUN. I respect your position. Germany and Italy have no conflict of interest: you dominate the Mediterranean and Balkans, I dominate the north. I propose a formal non-aggression pact and information sharing. Specifically: what are Austria and Russia doing in your theater? I can offer intelligence on England and France's movements in exchange. A coordinated approach benefits us both as the mid-game consolidates."}]
