ENG
[{'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "The HOL attack bounced last spring as GER held firm with KIE support - frustrating but expected. GER is now weakened with FRA holding BER and BUR. I propose we continue our coordination: I will move F NTH to HOL and F BEL supports, or alternatively F NTH to DEN while F BEL moves to HOL. GER has KIE, HOL, DEN, and BER - we need to crack them open. What are your intentions with A BER and A BUR this fall? If you push A BER to KIE and A BUR holds, I can take HOL with F BEL supported by F NTH. Let's finish GER off together and divide the spoils - HOL and DEN for me, KIE for you or vice versa."}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Germany, your position is precarious - FRA holds BER and BUR, threatening KIE from multiple angles. I have no interest in seeing FRA dominate the continent. If you are willing to cede HOL to me peacefully, I will use my naval forces to pressure FRA from the north and west, buying you breathing room to retake BER. A HOL can move to KIE or RUH to reinforce your position. This is a better outcome than losing everything to FRA. Consider it - a live GER with KIE and DEN is more useful to me than a dead one.'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, the continental balance is shifting dangerously - FRA now holds 6 centers including BER and MUN, making them the dominant power. I am working to contain them from the west but need assurance that you will pressure FRA's eastern flank or at minimum not interfere in Scandinavia. Our northern arrangement (NWY mine, SWE yours) remains solid. Are you coordinating with anyone against FRA? A strong FRA is bad for both of us."}]
