[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'The spring results confirm our coordination worked perfectly — A MUN took BER, your F BEL held position. Germany is now at three centers and bleeding. This fall I intend A BER - KIE to seize their last northern port, while A BUR holds to cover MUN. F MAO moves to support Atlantic flexibility. I need you to hold F BEL in place and keep F NTH covering the north — do not move into HOL yet, let me take KIE first and we can divide the German carcass cleanly. You get HOL and DEN, I get KIE and BER. That is a fair split and eliminates Germany entirely. Confirm you will hold BEL and NTH this fall.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Excellent work — A VIE is a strong position and Austria is finished. This fall I expect you to push A VIE - BUD to take that center while A VEN holds or moves to support. I am driving A BER - KIE to finish Germany. Our spheres remain clean: I stay out of BOH, TYR, and everything east of MUN; you stay out of MUN and the Rhine. Once Germany and Austria are eliminated we should discuss how to handle the eastern powers — Russia at five centers and Turkey at five is a problem neither of us can ignore alone. Let us finish our current targets first and then coordinate.'}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Germany, you are at three centers with A PAR, F KIE, A HOL — and I hold BER. The arithmetic is not in your favor. I am offering you one exit: cede KIE to me this fall without a fight, and I will support A PAR to hold against any English pressure and leave A HOL unmolested. You survive at two centers and have time to rebuild. Refuse, and I take KIE by force while England takes HOL simultaneously — you are eliminated by winter. This is not a bluff; England and I are coordinated. The choice is yours.'}]
