[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Confirmed - A GAL will NOT move to BUD this fall. I will hold GAL or move it elsewhere to avoid bouncing your attack on BUD. Italy takes BUD, Russia holds GAL and presses south toward RUM. Once Austria is finished, I agree: you take BUD and TRI, I take SER when I can reach it. This is a clean division. Let's execute."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Turkey, I hear your terms but cannot accept them in full. I will not move A SEV to ARM - that would expose my home center. However, I am moving A GAL away from your sphere this fall, and I have no intention of attacking ANK, CON, or SMY. RUM is a center I currently hold and will defend, but I am not advancing further into your territory. Italy at 6 centers is the existential threat to both of us - F ION is already in your waters. A RUS-TUR war while Italy expands is suicide for both of us. I propose a ceasefire: you keep BUL, GRE, BLA; I keep RUM and SEV. We both turn our attention to Italy.'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, I accept your logic - Italy is the dominant threat. I will not push into BUD this fall; Italy is attacking there and I will not interfere. Hold what you can. If you survive, we can coordinate against Italy's overextension in 1904. My A GAL will not move against you this phase."}]
