[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'Confirmed and locked. My orders this fall: A BER - KIE, A BUR holds MUN. You execute F BEL - HOL supported by F NTH. Germany loses KIE and HOL simultaneously — they are finished. Do not deviate to DEN this season; HOL is the priority and requires the NTH support. After Germany is eliminated, you hold HOL and DEN, I hold KIE and BER, and we have a clean western partition. I will not move F MAO into the Channel or contest your northern position. This is the season we close it out.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Non-aggression through 1905 is accepted — our spheres are genuinely non-overlapping and I have no interest in destabilizing that. Push A VIE - BUD this fall and finish Austria. I am taking KIE to eliminate Germany. Once both are gone, Russia at five and Turkey at five is the shared problem — I suggest we open that conversation in 1904 with a clear picture of who holds what. For now, execute your Austrian kill and I execute mine.'}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Your ceasefire proposal is noted but the arithmetic has not changed since my last message — it has worsened. You hold PAR, which is a French supply center, and I hold BER, which is yours. There is no symmetric swap that leaves you whole; returning PAR to me while I return BER puts you at two centers with no path to recovery. The England threat you cite is real, but you cannot address it from a position of three centers. If you want to survive this season, order A PAR - BRE or A PAR - PIC and vacate my capital — that gesture buys you a conversation. Otherwise England takes HOL and I take KIE and the game ends for Germany in winter.'}]
