[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Confirmed coordination this fall: I will move A GRE to SER to take that Austrian center, while F BLA holds to maintain Black Sea dominance and A CON repositions. I do NOT want F AEG moving toward SMY - keep it in AEG or move it to ION to pressure Austria's F ION. After Austria is eliminated, I propose a clean division: TUR sphere is GRE, BUL, RUM, SER, CON, ANK, SMY; ITA sphere is BUD, VIE, TRI, TUN, western Med. Russia is the next target - A SEV threatens my sphere and they hold 5 centers. Let's finish Austria first, then coordinate against Russia."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, your offer is rejected. RUM is mine - it was mine before you occupied it and it will be mine again. You have A SEV threatening my sphere and A GAL positioned aggressively. Here are my terms: move A SEV to UKR this fall and acknowledge RUM as Turkish territory, or I will move F BLA to SEV and begin dismantling your southern position. I am not interested in an anti-Italy coalition with a power that tried to steal BUL from me last year. Demonstrate good faith with concrete movement away from my centers, or face the consequences.'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, I appreciate your honesty about the Italian threat. However, I must be direct: I intend to move A GRE to SER this fall - SER is a natural extension of my Balkan sphere and I need it to build strength against Russia. I will not move on BUD this phase - that remains your center to defend. Regarding Italy, I agree they are dangerous at 6 centers, but I cannot coordinate militarily against them while Russia threatens my eastern flank. Focus your F ION on pressuring Italy's southern position - that is where you can hurt them most. Keep A BUD defended and we avoid conflict."}]
