[{'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'France, the situation has evolved significantly. You now hold 6 centers including BER, making you the dominant continental power. I hold DEN and BEL with fleets well-positioned. I propose we finish off Germany together this spring: I will move F DEN - KIE while F BEL - HOL, and you push A BER toward whatever target suits you. GER is down to 3 centers and cannot survive a coordinated assault. After GER falls, we can discuss a stable division of the north. What are your intended moves this phase?'}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, I'll be direct with you - France is the dominant threat now at 6 centers. I have no interest in destroying you completely; a weakened Germany serves as a useful buffer against French hegemony. If you can hold KIE and HOL, I will not press an attack this turn. Consider redirecting your forces to contest BER or BRE from France. A surviving Germany is more useful to Britain than a French-dominated continent. What can we arrange?"}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, France has surged to 6 centers and controls BER - they are becoming the dominant power in Europe. I am positioned in DEN and BEL with strong naval presence. I believe we should coordinate to contain French expansion. I can pressure GER's remaining centers to deny France further gains in the north, while you maintain pressure from the east. Are you open to an anti-French understanding? What are your intentions this spring?"}]
