[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "I must address what happened last fall directly - my F AEG attempted SMY, which you rightly opposed. I understand your frustration. Let me be clear about my intentions now: I have F AEG, A VIE, and A TRI positioned in the Balkans. I propose we coordinate against Austria's remaining forces. A BUD is mine to take, SER is yours if you push A GRE-SER. I will move F AEG to support your operations or hold in AEG as a buffer - I will NOT move to SMY this season. Austria must be finished. What are your planned moves so we can coordinate properly?"}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, the situation is favorable for both of us. Austria is nearly finished - I hold VIE and TRI, you have GAL pressing BUD. I intend to push A VIE-BUD this season to eliminate Austria entirely. I ask that A GAL support my A VIE-BUD move, or at minimum not contest BUD yourself. In return, I acknowledge RUM as your sphere and will not interfere with your Balkan expansion eastward. Turkey is growing fast with 6 centers - we should both be watching them carefully. What are your intentions this season?'}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'France, our non-aggression holds and I intend to honor it through 1905 as agreed. I am focused entirely on finishing Austria and managing the eastern situation. Turkey now holds 6 centers and is the fastest-growing power in the east - something we should both monitor. Germany is weakened at 3 centers. I see no conflict between our spheres of influence. What is your plan for this season - continuing pressure on Germany?'}]
