[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, the board is developing well for both of us. Austria is nearly finished - A BUD and F NAP are all they have left. I propose we coordinate to eliminate Austria entirely this spring: I will move A GAL to BUD to take it, while you push A VIE toward TRI or support the attack. Once Austria is gone, we can divide the Balkans cleanly. I also intend to move A SEV toward RUM to pressure Turkey, who has been openly hostile to me. Turkey at 6 centers is a growing threat to both of us - your F AEG is well-positioned to contest the Aegean. Let's discuss a coordinated anti-Turkey push after Austria falls."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, we have been at odds but the current board position demands pragmatism. Italy now holds VIE and TRI, and has F AEG threatening your SMY. Italy at 5+ centers is a greater threat to you than Russia. I propose a ceasefire: I will not move A SEV to ARM or attack your positions if you keep F BLA away from SEV. We can both focus on containing Italy's expansion. I am willing to discuss a formal non-aggression arrangement if you are interested in stabilizing the eastern front."}, {'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "England, the western situation is chaotic with France dominating at 6 centers including BER. France is the clear leader and must be contained. I hold SWE and can threaten DEN or NWY if needed to pressure the north, but I'd prefer we coordinate. What are your plans this spring? I am focused on the Balkans but want to ensure our northern arrangement remains stable. F SWE will not threaten your positions."}]
