[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Your F AEG moved toward SMY last fall - a direct attack on my home center. I blocked it with A CON-SMY. Let me be direct: if you persist in attacking my home centers, I will dedicate every unit I have to destroying you. However, I am willing to reset. ITA and TUR have natural complementary spheres - you dominate the western Balkans and Adriatic, I dominate the eastern Balkans and Black Sea. I propose: F AEG moves to ION or EAS, away from my territory. In return, I will not contest TRI or VIE, and I will actively support your position against Austria. We can both grow without fighting each other. What do you say?'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, Italy is your existential threat - they hold VIE and TRI and will finish you unless we coordinate. I am prepared to move A GRE to SER this spring to take that center and pressure Italy's flank. I need you to confirm: where is F NAP moving? If you can threaten Italy from the south while I push from SER, we can contain their expansion. I am not your enemy - Italy is. Let us coordinate specifically: I take SER, you use F NAP to threaten Italian supply lines. Confirm your moves."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, the situation has changed. Italy has become the dominant power with 6 centers and is actively attacking my home territory. I am willing to discuss a genuine ceasefire. I will not move on SEV if you keep A SEV out of ARM and do not threaten BUL or RUM. We both benefit from containing Italy before they reach 7-8 centers and become unstoppable. I am not asking for an alliance - just mutual non-aggression while we each deal with our respective threats. Can you agree to hold A SEV in place this spring?'}]
