[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Comrade, the situation is dire but recoverable. France holds BER and MUN - my home centers - while England sits in DEN and BEL threatening HOL. I need your active support. I propose: if you can pressure GAL or SIL to tie down French forces, I can focus my three units on retaking BER and threatening BRE. Specifically, can you move A GAL toward SIL this turn? That would force France to defend rather than advance. In return, I pledge no German units east of Berlin - your western flank is safe. We must coordinate now or France dominates the board. What can you commit to?'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, you've made impressive gains in Vienna and Trieste. France is now the dominant power with 6 centers including both Berlin and Munich - this threatens everyone. I propose we coordinate: I will push hard on France from the west (BRE, PAR) while you pressure from the south. France cannot defend on two fronts simultaneously. What are your intentions this spring? I can offer intelligence and coordination against our common threat. Austria is weakened - perhaps we can discuss a division of remaining Austrian centers as well."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'France, you hold BER and MUN - my home centers - while I hold BRE, your home center. We are at an impasse that benefits neither of us. England grows stronger while we bleed each other. I propose a ceasefire: I return BRE, you return BER. MUN remains contested but we halt further aggression. This allows both of us to focus on England who now holds DEN, BEL, NWY, EDI, LON, LVP - six centers and growing. If you refuse, I will burn BRE to the ground before surrendering it and coordinate with Russia and Italy against you. The choice is yours.'}]
