[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'The board position entering 1904: France holds BER, PAR, MAO. Germany holds BRE with A BRE and KIE with F KIE — they are a rump state occupying my home center. I intend A BER - KIE this season to finish them. I need your F DEN to support A BER - KIE, or at minimum hold DEN and not interfere. In exchange, I will not contest HOL, BEL, or DEN — those are yours. Once Germany is eliminated, we should discuss the eastern situation. Confirm your intentions for F DEN and F BEL this season.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, the board is moving fast. You hold VIE and TRI — Austria is finished. I am taking KIE this season to eliminate Germany. My concern is Turkey at six centers and growing. Once Austria collapses and Germany is gone, Turkey becomes the dominant eastern power. I propose we coordinate: I will stay entirely out of your sphere (TYR, BOH, eastern Med), and you should consider whether your A VIE or A TRI can begin pressuring toward BUD or the Balkans to contain Turkish expansion. What is your plan for the Austrian remnants and the Turkish threat?'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, France is eliminating Germany this season. England sits at six centers with a strong naval position — HOL, DEN, BEL, NWY plus home centers. That is a power that will dominate the north if unchecked. I am not in a position to threaten England from the west alone. You hold SWE adjacent to DEN. I am not asking for immediate action, but I want to open a channel: what is your read on English intentions in the north, and are you open to discussing coordination against English overreach in 1905?'}]
