[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, final offer before orders lock: I have A BUD and F NAP. If you press BUD, I move F NAP to ROM immediately - you lose a home center. If you hold A VIE and A TRI in place, I hold A BUD and move F NAP to ION or TYS, away from your territory. This is a simple exchange: you get security in the south, I survive one more turn. Attacking me costs you ROM. Is that trade worth it to you?'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, I am moving A BUD to RUM this turn to take that Turkish center - it is undefended and adjacent. I need you to move A GAL to BUD to support my survival, or at minimum hold A GAL in place and not attack me. Italy is the real threat to both of us. If I fall, Italy reaches 8 centers and becomes unstoppable. Help me survive and I will coordinate against Italy with you going forward. F NAP can threaten Italian southern centers while you press from the north.'}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Turkey, I see your offer but I will not hand you SER for free - that is my last viable territory. Here is what I will do: F NAP moves to ION this turn, threatening Italian positions in the south. A BUD moves to RUM - your center, yes, but you have plenty of others and this keeps me alive to fight Italy. If you want coordination against Italy, accept that I need RUM to survive. A dead Austria helps no one. I am not your enemy - let me take RUM and we both pressure Italy.'}]
