[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "I accept your assurance that F AEG will not move to SMY this season. Here are my confirmed moves: A GRE-SER (taking that center from Austria), F BLA holds (maintaining Black Sea control), A CON holds or repositions. I expect F AEG to remain in AEG or move to ION - any move toward SMY or EAS will be treated as an act of war and I will redirect all my forces against you. If you honor this, we can coordinate properly against Austria's remnants and I will not contest TRI or VIE. Let us both grow without fighting - confirm F AEG's destination."}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, I am moving A GRE-SER this spring - this takes SER and pressures Italy's flank directly. I need you to use F NAP aggressively against Italian supply lines in the south - move toward ION or threaten TUN. Italy holds VIE and TRI and will eliminate you unless we act now. I am your best hope for survival: I take SER, you threaten Italy from NAP, and together we deny Italy the Balkan dominance they seek. Confirm F NAP's move so I can plan accordingly."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, I agree to the ceasefire terms: F BLA will not move to SEV, and I expect A SEV to remain in SEV and not move to ARM or threaten BUL/RUM. Italy is the primary threat to both of us - they have 6 centers and are positioned to dominate. I am moving A GRE-SER this phase to contain Italian Balkan expansion. If you can apply pressure from GAL toward Austrian or Italian positions, we both benefit. This is not an alliance - it is mutual non-aggression while we each address our threats. Hold A SEV in place and we have a deal.'}]
